Adjust racks to top and middle positions and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Trim, peel, and cut @carrots{12%ounce} on a diagonal into 1/2-inch-thick pieces. Dice @potatoes{12%ounce} into 1/2-inch pieces. Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}, separating whites from greens.

Trim and discard woody bottom ends from @asparagus{6%ounce}. (Save carrots for another use.)

Toss carrots on a #baking sheet{} with a large drizzle of @olive oil{}, half the @Fry Seasoning{1%tablespoon} (all for 4 servings), @salt{}, and @pepper{}. Roast on top rack until golden brown and tender, ~{20-25%minutes}.

> Swap in asparagus for carrots; roast until lightly browned and tender, about 10-12 minutes.

While carrots roast, place potatoes in a #medium pot{} with enough salted water to cover by 2 inches. Bring to a boil and cook until tender, ~{15-20%minutes}.

Reserve 1/2 cup potato cooking liquid; drain and return potatoes to pot. Mash with one packet @sour cream{2.5%tablespoon} and 1 TBSP @butter{1%tablespoon} until smooth, adding splashes of reserved potato cooking liquid as needed.

Stir in half the scallion greens. Season with salt and pepper. Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

Meanwhile, pat @chicken cutlets{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}; season with salt and pepper.

Place @butter{1%tablespoon} in a shallow #microwave-safe dish{}. Microwave until melted, ~{30%seconds}. Stir in @Panko Breadcrumbs{1/4%cup}, @Frank's Seasoning Blend{1/4%ounce}, and a pinch of salt and pepper.

Brush one packet sour cream onto tops of chicken in a thin layer. Working one piece at a time, dip brushed sides of chicken into panko mixture, pressing to adhere (no need to coat the undersides). Place chicken, coated sides up, on a second, lightly oiled baking sheet.

Roast chicken on middle rack until browned and cooked through, ~{15-18%minutes}. Transfer to a #plate{} to rest.

While chicken cooks, in a #small bowl{}, combine @Blue Cheese Dressing{1.5%ounce}, scallion whites, and remaining sour cream.

Divide carrots, mashed potatoes, and chicken between plates. Top chicken with blue cheese sauce, remaining scallion greens, and @?hot sauce{1%teaspoon} if desired. Serve with any remaining blue cheese sauce on the side.

> Chicken is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.